  "body": {
    "export_view": {
      "value": "<p>By default, an inventory item with no stock availability cannot be added to a ticket. This is to ensure that your location cannot oversell your inventory to customers. Admins can allow for backorder items at the company or level. If a user adds an inventory item that is not in stock to a ticket and update/save the ticket status, the system will create a new, placeholder entry into your inventory with <strong>Back</strong> <strong>Ordered</strong> status. A ticket with a backorder item cannot be closed until you have fulfilled the order.</p><p>Backorder items can be fulfilled manually or automatically through a Purchase Order (PO) replenishment. If the same item has been back ordered on multiple tickets, the PO will fulfill older tickets first.</p><p>RepairQ includes features to notify managers on the dashboard when backorder items are added to tickets, and the PO also includes reordering notifications, to help you replenish these orders first.</p><h3 id=\"InventoryManagement:AllowforBackorderInventoryonTickets-AdditionalResources\">Additional Resources</h3><ul><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1933705356/Getting+Started+The+RepairQ+Dashboard\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1933705356\" data-linked-resource-version=\"9\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Getting Started: The RepairQ Dashboard</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1933246673/Checking+for+Items+that+Require+Reordering\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1933246673\" data-linked-resource-version=\"4\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Checking for Items that Require Reordering</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1933312056/Inventory+Management+Stock+a+Backorder+Item+With+a+Purchase+Order\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1933312056\" data-linked-resource-version=\"5\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Inventory Management: Stock a Backorder Item With a Purchase Order</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1933967395/Inventory+Management+Stock+a+Backorder+Item+Without+a+Purchase+Order\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1933967395\" data-linked-resource-version=\"4\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Inventory Management: Stock a Backorder Item Without a Purchase Order</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1932624055/Inventory+Status+Overview\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1932624055\" data-linked-resource-version=\"7\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Inventory Status - What Does It Mean?</a></p></li></ul><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"680\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933672497/Instructional%20-%200091cd.png?api=v2\"></span><h2 id=\"InventoryManagement:AllowforBackorderInventoryonTickets-AuthorizeYourLocationtoCreateBackorderItemsonTickets\">Authorize Your Location to Create Backorder Items on Tickets</h2><p /><p>On the Navigation Bar, go to <strong>Settings</strong> \u2192 <strong>Location Settings</strong>. On the Settings Overview page, under the Tickets section, click <strong>General Settings</strong>.</p><p><strong>Note</strong>: This setting can also be authorized at the Company (Global) level by going to <strong>Company Settings</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" width=\"760\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933672497/Backorder%201.png?api=v2\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" alt=\"Backorder 5.png\" width=\"760\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933672497/Backorder%205.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><h3 id=\"InventoryManagement:AllowforBackorderInventoryonTickets-TicketGeneralSettings\">Ticket General Settings</h3><p>On the General Settings page, toggle the setting for <strong>Auto-backorder out-of-stock items</strong> to <strong>ON </strong>and <strong>Save </strong>your settings. </p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" alt=\"Backorder 6.png\" width=\"380\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933672497/Backorder%206.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>When this setting is activated, you can add out-of-stock items as Back Ordered on tickets. This item must be replenished before the ticket can be closed.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" alt=\"Backorder 8.png\" width=\"760\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933672497/Backorder%208.png?api=v2\"></span><hr/><h2 id=\"InventoryManagement:AllowforBackorderInventoryonTickets-TicketStatusAdvancementforBackorderItems\">Ticket Status Advancement for Backorder Items</h2><p>You can configure how tickets advance between statuses based on whether a backordered item is present. In <strong>Location Settings \u2192 Ticket General Settings</strong>, you can restrict ticket progression to certain statuses or limit it by ticket type. These settings help control workflow by preventing tickets with backordered items from advancing until the necessary stock is available.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" alt=\"Backorder 7.png\" width=\"380\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933672497/Backorder%207.png?api=v2\"></span><ul><li><p><strong>Do Not Allow On</strong> \u2013 Enables or disables the restriction.</p></li><li><p><strong>Ticket Statuses</strong> \u2013 Specifies which statuses cannot be selected if the ticket contains a backordered item. By default, you cannot close a ticket with a backorder item.</p></li><li><p><strong>Ticket Types</strong> \u2013 Specifies which ticket types cannot be saved if a backordered item is present.</p></li></ul><p /><p /><p>START 1.22.X</p>",
